The Security Operations Center (SOC) performance was evaluated using key metrics including Mean Time to Detect (MTTD), Mean Time to Respond (MTTR), and false positive rate. The MTTD was observed at 2 hours, indicating moderate detection efficiency, while the MTTR was recorded at 4 hours, suggesting delays in incident response processes. Additionally, a false positive rate of 15% highlights the need for improved alert tuning and filtering mechanisms.

These findings suggest that while the SOC has a functional detection capability, there is room for optimization in response speed and alert accuracy. To enhance overall performance, it is recommended to implement automated response workflows, improve threat intelligence integration, and fine-tune detection rules within Elastic Security. Regular monitoring and continuous improvement of these metrics will help strengthen the organization’s security posture and reduce incident impact.
